article.headline: Hawaii 65, Louisiana Tech 64
article.story: HONOLULU -- Bill Amis scored 17 points and hit the game-winning basket with 8.1 seconds left Monday night as Hawaii beat Louisiana Tech 65-64. Down 64-63, Kareem Nitoto drove the lane and passed to Amis, who made a jumper from the baseline to give the Rainbow Warriors the lead. Louisiana Techs Kyle Gibson missed a jumper just inside the 3-point line with two seconds left. Paul Campbell, Roderick Flemings and Adhar Mayen scored 13 points apiece for Hawaii (9-5, 1-1 Western Athletic Conference). Kenneth Cooper scored 14 to lead Louisiana Tech (7-8, 1-1). Hawaii led by 13 in the first half, but the Bulldogs used a 10-2 run late in the second half to take its first lead of the game 61-60 after a Magnum Rolle jumper with 2:42 remaining. The Bulldogs extended the lead to 64-60 before Nitoto hit a 3-pointer and set up Amis's game winner.
